<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="mathml.xsl"?><html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><title>glIsQuery</title><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.69.1" /></head><body><div class="refentry" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="glIsQuery"></a><div class="titlepage"></div><div class="refnamediv"><h2>Name</h2><p>glIsQuery — determine if a name corresponds to a query object</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>C Specification</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> GLboolean <b class="fsfunc">glIsQuery</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">id</var><code>)</code>;<br /> GLuint <var class="pdparam">id</var>;</p></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781743"></a><h2>PARAMETERS</h2><div class="variablelist"><dl><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>id</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Specifies a value that may be the name of a query object.
                </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781635"></a><h2>DESCRIPTION</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glIsQuery</code> returns <code class="constant">GL_TRUE</code> if <em class="parameter"><code>id</code></em> is currently the name of a query object.
            If <em class="parameter"><code>id</code></em> is zero, or is a non-zero value that is not currently the
            name of a query object, or if an error occurs, <code class="function">glIsQuery</code> returns <code class="constant">GL_FALSE</code>.
        </p><p>
            A name returned by <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glGenQueries</span></span>, but not yet associated with a query object
            by calling <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glBeginQuery</span></span>, is not the name of a query object.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4768240"></a><h2>NOTES</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glIsQuery</code> is available only if the GL version is 1.5 or greater.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4768256"></a><h2>ERRORS</h2><p>
            <code class="constant">GL_INVALID_OPERATION</code> is generated if <code class="function">glIsQuery</code> is executed
            between the execution of <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glBegin</span></span> and the corresponding
            execution of <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glEnd</span></span>.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4768288"></a><h2>SEE ALSO</h2><p>
            <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glBeginQuery</span></span>,
            <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glDeleteQueries</span></span>,
            <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glEndQuery</span></span>,
            <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glGenQueries</span></span>
